<task id="WKSP-002" project="spaarke-workspace-user-configuration-r1">
  <metadata>
    <title>Define layout template configurations</title>
    <phase>1</phase>
    <tags>shared-components, types</tags>
    <estimated-effort>2h</estimated-effort>
    <rigor-level>STANDARD</rigor-level>
    <dependencies>WKSP-001</dependencies>
    <parallel-group>serial</parallel-group>
    <parallel-safe>true</parallel-safe>
  </metadata>
  <prompt>
    <role>Senior TypeScript/C# developer implementing workspace personalization</role>
    <goal>Define the LayoutTemplate type and 6 layout template constants that describe the available grid arrangements users can choose in the Layout Wizard.</goal>
    <context>
      The workspace personalization feature allows users to pick a layout template that defines the grid
      structure of their dashboard. Each template specifies named slots arranged in rows and columns using
      CSS grid. The Layout Wizard (Phase 5) will present these as visual thumbnails.

      The existing WorkspaceShell already supports a "rows" layout variant with WorkspaceRowConfig defining
      gridTemplateColumns per row. Layout templates formalize this: each template is a constant object with
      an id, human-readable name, description, a rows array (each row has column definitions and slot names),
      and total slot count.

      Templates to define:
      1. "2-col-equal" — 2 rows: top row 2 equal columns, bottom row 2 equal columns (4 slots)
      2. "3-row-mixed" — 3 rows: top 2-col, middle full-width, bottom 2-col (5 slots) [current default]
      3. "sidebar-main" — 2 columns: narrow sidebar (1fr) + wide main (2fr), 3 rows each side (6 slots)
      4. "single-column" — 4 stacked full-width rows (4 slots)
      5. "3-col-equal" — 2 rows of 3 equal columns each (6 slots)
      6. "hero-grid" — hero full-width top row + 3-col bottom row (4 slots)
    </context>
    <constraints>
      - All types and constants MUST be in @spaarke/ui-components shared library (ADR-012)
      - LayoutTemplate type MUST include: id, name, description, rows (array with columns + slot definitions), slotCount
      - Each row definition MUST include gridTemplateColumns (CSS value) and slots (array of slot identifiers)
      - Template IDs MUST be stable string literals used as discriminators in Dataverse storage
      - MUST export both the type and the LAYOUT_TEMPLATES constant array from the barrel
      - MUST NOT depend on any runtime code — these are pure data constants
    </constraints>
  </prompt>
  <knowledge>
    <files>
      <file>.claude/adr/ADR-012-shared-components.md</file>
      <file>src/client/shared/Spaarke.UI.Components/src/components/WorkspaceShell/types.ts</file>
    </files>
  </knowledge>
  <relevant-files>
    <file>src/client/shared/Spaarke.UI.Components/src/components/WorkspaceShell/types.ts</file>
    <file>src/client/shared/Spaarke.UI.Components/src/components/WorkspaceShell/</file>
    <file>src/client/shared/Spaarke.UI.Components/src/index.ts</file>
  </relevant-files>
  <steps>
    <step id="1">Read existing WorkspaceRowConfig type to understand the gridTemplateColumns pattern and ensure layout templates align with the existing row model.</step>
    <step id="2">Define LayoutTemplateRow interface with: slots (string array of slot identifiers like "slot-1", "slot-2"), gridTemplateColumns (CSS string), and optional gridTemplateColumnsSmall (responsive override).</step>
    <step id="3">Define LayoutTemplate interface with: id (string literal union type), name (string), description (string), rows (LayoutTemplateRow[]), slotCount (number), and thumbnail (optional string for preview image path).</step>
    <step id="4">Define the LayoutTemplateId string union type for all 6 template IDs: "2-col-equal" | "3-row-mixed" | "sidebar-main" | "single-column" | "3-col-equal" | "hero-grid".</step>
    <step id="5">Create the 6 template constant objects with correct grid definitions. Ensure "3-row-mixed" matches the current LegalWorkspace default layout (row1: 2-col 1fr 1fr, row2: full-width, row3: 2-col 1fr 1fr).</step>
    <step id="6">Export LAYOUT_TEMPLATES as a readonly array and a getLayoutTemplate(id) lookup helper function.</step>
    <step id="7">Update barrel exports and verify TypeScript compilation succeeds.</step>
  </steps>
  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion>LayoutTemplate and LayoutTemplateId types are exported from @spaarke/ui-components</criterion>
    <criterion>LAYOUT_TEMPLATES constant array contains exactly 6 template definitions</criterion>
    <criterion>"3-row-mixed" template matches the current LegalWorkspace default: row1 (1fr 1fr), row2 (1fr full), row3 (1fr 1fr) with 5 slots</criterion>
    <criterion>getLayoutTemplate(id) returns the matching template or undefined</criterion>
    <criterion>TypeScript compilation succeeds with no errors</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>
</task>
